subSubSection.paragraph:
Recognised in the genus 

Maesa

by the following combination of characters: the scrambling habit, lacking hairs but with scales throughout, obovate leaves, simple to compound racemose inflorescences and pentamerous flowers with distinctive narrowly triangular bracteoles;

